# SAS 9.4 Silent Installation — Intune Deployment Script

A PowerShell script for silently deploying SAS 9.4 M9 (Teaching & Research) to managed Windows endpoints via Microsoft Intune. Designed for higher education and enterprise environments where SAS must be deployed at scale without user IT involvement.

---

## Overview

Manual SAS installation is time-consuming, error-prone, and requires elevated privileges most end users don't have. This script packages the entire installation workflow — user prompting, file staging, silent execution, and Intune detection — into a single deployable unit.

**What it does:**
- Detects whether SAS 9.4 is already installed (skips if detected)
- Copies installer files from a network share to local temp using `robocopy` (handles Windows long path limitations)
- Prompts the active user session with an install/postpone dialog before proceeding
- Runs the SAS Deployment Manager silently using a pre-configured response file
- Writes a registry detection key so Intune knows the installation succeeded
- Logs everything — locally and to a network share — for troubleshooting

