## Configuration

At the top of `SAS_Install_2026.ps1`, update the `$Config` hashtable for your environment:

```powershell
$LicenseYear = "2026"   # Update each renewal cycle

$Config = @{
    NetworkInstallerPath = "\\your-fileserver\share\SAS_Installer_2026\SAS94_Install_Files"
    LogsRootNetwork      = "\\your-fileserver\share\Logs\SAS_Install_2026_Logs"
    StagingRoot          = "C:\Temp\SAS_Install_2026"
    InstallDestination   = "C:\Program Files\SASHome"
    PostponeHours        = 2
    InstallTimeout       = 7200   # seconds (2 hours)
    PromptTimeout        = 3600   # seconds (1 hour before re-prompt)
}
```

### Response file

The `sas94m9install.properties` file must point to the license file at the **local staging path**, not the network share — because the setup.exe runs after files are copied locally:

```properties
INSTALLER_UI=silent
SAS_INSTALLATION_DATA=C:\\Temp\\SAS_Install_2026\\SAS_94_TR_2026_License.txt
SAS_INSTALL_DIR=C:\\Program Files\\SASHome
QUIET_MODE=true
```

